Consider the wave equation

\begin{align*}
u_{tt} = u_{xx} , \,
\end{align*} with initial conditions

\begin{align*}
u(x,0) = f(x) = \begin{cases}
 2 \sin(2x) & 0 < x < \pi \\
 0 & \text{otherwise}
 \end{cases}, \;\; u_t(x,0) = 0.
\end{align*}

(b) Suppose instead the domain is the interval $[0,\pi]$, with zero
(Dirichlet) boundary conditions:

\begin{align*}
u(0,t) = 0 = u(\pi,t) , \,
\end{align*} and find the solution by separation of
variables.
